<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-101-242  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 101 242.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  Nov 27 1989 v3 n48 p3(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Congress suspends procurement integrity law until next year.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Rivenbank, Leigh.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The procurement integrity law has been suspended by Congress forone year after having been attached to Congress's own pay raiseand ethics package; the suspension comes two weeks after thecontroversial law had been clarified and one day after the Househad voted for its repeal.andP;  Some lawmakers claim the suspension istacit approval of exchanging source-selection information forfavors from government contractors, while others claim the law isso vague that it would never result in any successful prosecution.andO;Sources on Capitol Hill report that Pres Bush insisted on repealof the procurement integrity law in exchange for his signingCongress's pay raise package, but he will settle for the one-yearsuspension.andP;  The law limits the ability of federal employees todiscuss jobs with contractors or potential contractors and ismeant to stop government workers moving to jobs with thecontractors.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     LegislationNational GovernmentGovernment ContractsEthicsCompetitive BiddingGovernment OfficialsContractorsPolitical IssuesEmployment.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>